text:
I can't make use of the (faster) drawImage(BufferedImage, BufferedImageOp, int,
int) call on the Graphics2D class, since, whenever I am rendering to SVG, this
throws NullPointerExceptions every time.

This is a simple fix, just change line 995 from:
img = op.filter(img, null);

to

if (op!=null){
  img = op.filter(img, null);
}
